article.description: Erica Wheeler scored 15 points to help Rutgers (No. 12 ESPN/USA Today, No. 11 AP) remain unbeaten with a 63-49 win over Florida on Friday night.
article.headline: Rutgers tops Florida, continues best start since 2005
article.linkText: Rutgers improves to 8-0 for first time since '05
article.story:
DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. -- Erica Wheeler scored 15 points to help Rutgers (No. 12 ESPN/USA Today, No. 11 AP) remain unbeaten with a 63-49 win over Florida on Friday night.

April Sykes and Monique Oliver added 12 points each, and Betnijah Laney had 10 for the Scarlet Knights, who are off to their first 8-0 start since 2005.

Jordan Jones scored 20 points to lead turnover-plagued Florida (6-2), which hit only 2 of its first 11 shots to open the second half and committed 22 miscues that Rutgers turned into 22 points.

Deana Allen added 11 points for the Gators, who snapped a six-game win streak.
